qas.question: How many sub components are there?

plausible_answers.text: Primary Reserve, Supplementary Reserve, Cadet Organizations Administration and Training Service, and the Canadian Rangers.

qas.question: What four components make up the Force Reserve?
What is the Canadian Armed Forces associated with under the National Defence Act?
How many non-sub components are there?
What act does not define the CAF?

context: This unified institution consists of sea, land, and air elements referred to as the <b2_0>Royal Canadian Navy<b2_0/> (RCN), Canadian Army, and <b3_0>Royal Canadian Air Force<b3_0/> (RCAF). Personnel may belong to either the Regular Force or the Reserve Force, which has <a0_0><b6_0>four<b6_0/><a0_0/> sub-components: the <b4_0>Primary Reserve, Supplementary Reserve, Cadet Organizations Administration and Training Service, and the Canadian Rangers.<b4_0/> Under <a1_0>the <b7_0>National Defence Act<b7_0/><a1_0/>, the Canadian Armed Forces are an entity separate and distinct from the <b5_0>Department of National Defence<b5_0/> (the federal government department responsible for administration and formation of defence policy), which also exists as the civilian support system for the Forces.
